{
  "texts": [
    "AI's ability to combine and analyze data from both sensory systems enhances our understanding of complex phenomena such as sensory loss, multisensory integration, and flavor identification.",
    "The findings underscore the transformative role of AI in advancing the science of smell and taste, offering innovative solutions to long-standing challenges.",
    "While these applications span a wide range of domains, they are supported by diverse computational strategies tailored to the specific characteristics of olfactory and gustatory data.",
    "For instance, certain tasks may require models that handle high-dimensional chemical input, while others demand sensitivity to subtle temporal changes in sensory responses.",
    "These different requirements have led to the adoption of a variety of artificial intelligence approaches, each designed to address unique technical and practical challenges."
  ]
}